articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: New Zealand's justice minister resigned on Monday after being arrested in relation to a car crash the previous day, the fourth minister to quit the cabinet in as many months in an election year.
articles.title: New Zealand justice minister quits after being charged following car crash

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The mayor of the Ecuadorian Pacific port city of Manta, Agustin Intriago, was assassinated on Sunday, authorities said, in a brazen attack that stunned the political establishment.
articles.title: Mayor of Ecuadorian city of Manta assassinated in brazen attack

articles.author: Simon Lewis
articles.description: The United States said it was pausing some foreign assistance programs in Cambodia and imposing visa bans on individuals it says undermined democracy after the ruling Cambodian People's Party (CPP) declared a landslide victory in elections on Sunday.
articles.title: US pauses some aid, imposes visa bans after 'neither free nor fair' Cambodia election

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Clashes flared in parts of Sudan on the 100th day of the war on Sunday as mediation attempts by regional and international powers fail to find a path out of an increasingly intractable conflict.
articles.title: Sudan war enters 100th day as mediation attempts fail

articles.author: Nia Williams
articles.description: Canada's East Coast province of Nova Scotia began cleaning up on Sunday after torrential rainfall caused devastating floods, while the search continued for four people including two children who went missing during the deluge.
articles.title: Nova Scotia wrestles with aftermath of devastating floods

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The concrete roof of a school gymnasium collapsed in China's Qiqihar city on Sunday killing 10 people, with one person still trapped, state media reported on Monday.
articles.title: Ten killed after school gymnasium roof collapses in China

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia withdrew from the Black Sea grain deal that ensured the safe export of Ukrainian grains because the agreement lost its meaning, President Vladimir Putin wrote in an article published early on Monday.
articles.title: Russia's Putin: Black Sea grain deal became meaningless

articles.author: Belén Carreño, Emma Pinedo
articles.description: Spain was heading for a hung parliament, with neither left nor right likely to secure a majority in the Sunday election, paving the way for drawn-out and potentially fruitless negotiations to form a government.
articles.title: Spanish election's nail-biting finish makes hung parliament likely

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A wildfire which has raged on the Greek island of Rhodes for six days forced thousands of tourists and island residents to shelter in schools and indoor stadiums on Sunday after they were evacuated from coastal villages and resorts.
articles.title: Tourists flee Greek island Rhodes wildfire, thousands evacuated

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Police in Ohio unleashed a canine on a Black man who had exited his vehicle with his hands raised after a traffic stop earlier this month, according to officials.
articles.title: Black man attacked by Ohio police dog during traffic stop
